{"key":"post-9886533","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9886533</id>\n<content>I wish you guys would say what is INSIDE the bags.&amp;nbsp; Bags are just plastic and have nothing to colonize.&amp;nbsp; However, if the 'bag' is filled with manure or other bulk substrate with a bit of grains on top, you want your spores going directly to the grains as much as possible.&amp;nbsp; Once the grains are fully colonized, knead the bags to spread the colonized grains around to the rest of the substrate.&amp;nbsp; Flame sterilize the needles and ALWAYS use a glove box or laminar flow hood for best success rate.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9886564</next>\n<prev>9886511</prev>\n<first>9885117</first>\n<last>9900474</last>\n<when>1235875915</when>\n<utime>03/01/09 04:51 AM</utime>\n</post>"}